	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK people, some of you have apparently gotten the wrong impression somewhere.<BR>
<BR>
1.  This spell will not cause ALL the mobs to aggro you, I have aggroed more mobs with heal spells than this one (remember, MOBs treat heals as direct damage, so a &quot;Healing&quot; spell is treated as a 75 damage AOE spell)  I have aggroed at most 3 MOBS with this spell, and the tanks could get them off without using taunt.<BR>
<BR>
2.  At 19 you SHOULD still be meleeing.  Those defence skills you are letting atropy at this low level WILL come back to haunt you later.  (Imagine running from a lvl 40-50 mob with a 30 dodge skill as opposed to a 200, at the high levels 1 dodge could be the difference between life and death.  Also, your casting is NOT interupted if the MOB misses you or you dodge)<BR>
<BR>
3.  At this low level you should be practicing teaming with more than one healer in your party.  At later levels, you'll get dumped quick for steping on the other cleric's spells.  This means one cleric can nuke and melee while the other heals, and a quick AOE spell might take some of the MOBs off the primary healer.<BR>
<BR>
4.  Enchanters, Wizards, Magicians, Necros, and Druids ALL have less ac, hp, and sta than you (if they don't, maybe you should reconsider your char) and they know how to effectively use their AOE.  If these naked casters can do it even at lvl 60, what makes you think a fully armed and armored Cleric can't at lvl 19?<BR>
<BR>
A final word of advice.  Don't use the AOE spells with an Enchanter in the group, breaking MEZ on a 15 MOB train is a BAD idea whatever the level.<BR>
<BR>
BTW this spell works wonders interupting MOB casters.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
