			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have actually found AoE spells useful when soloing.  I have been using WoP against the Sisters in LFay to good effect.  I usually try to pull just one at a time using Soothe, but when a pull goes awry, you can fight the toughest one and just keep trying to get this spell off.  You have the whole mob anyway.  I took on a blue and two high greens that way.  Once the blue was out of the way, I was able to use WoP to get the other two down really fast.<BR>
<BR>
I was also helping a friend get some experience and used it's pulling effect to get a mob off him that he couldn't handle.  Healing him didn't pull them since we were not grouped, but an AoE spell sure will.  The disadvantage here is the long casting time.  Have to cast it and get the mob off before your friend dies.
				</font>
			</td>

